webpackJsonp([0x8fe5f7c379f0],{683:function(n,s){n.exports={data:{post:{id:"E:/gatsby-starter-personal-blog/content/posts/2017-06-19--unreal-engine-coding-standards-part-iii/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-fff2860b5d54444bf119ca3d0101d009-36d56.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 45.24772497472194%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;"\n        alt="Unreal Engine Coding Standards"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-fff2860b5d54444bf119ca3d0101d009-78f2b.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-fff2860b5d54444bf119ca3d0101d009-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-fff2860b5d54444bf119ca3d0101d009-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-fff2860b5d54444bf119ca3d0101d009-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-fff2860b5d54444bf119ca3d0101d009-ab4c4.jpg 1200w,\n/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-fff2860b5d54444bf119ca3d0101d009-bc99b.jpg 1600w,\n/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-fff2860b5d54444bf119ca3d0101d009-36d56.jpg 1978w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Learn C++ from scratch. How to make your first video game in Unreal engine. Gain confidence in programming.\nThis is a fork of the Part I of the first section of the <a href="https://github.com/UnrealCourse">Unreal Course</a> teaching C++ coding standards for the Unreal Game Engine.\nThe Source Code can be found in <a href="https://github.com/mpolinowski/consoleApplication">consoleApplication</a>\nThe following is the commented Course Journal:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<!-- TOC -->\n<ul>\n<li><a href="#iterating-with-for--while-loops">Iterating With For &#x26; While Loops</a></li>\n<li><a href="#clarity-is-worth-fighting-for">Clarity is Worth Fighting For</a></li>\n<li><a href="#booleans-and-comparisons">Booleans and comparisons</a></li>\n<li><a href="#using-do-and-while-in-c">Using do and while in C++</a></li>\n</ul>\n<!-- /TOC -->\n<h3 id="iterating-with-for--while-loops"><a href="#iterating-with-for--while-loops" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Iterating With For &#x26; While Loops</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Use loops to prevent typing the same code repeatedly</li>\n<li>When to use <strong>for</strong> vs <strong>while</strong> -> “When you know what you in <strong>FOR</strong>” / “When you are looping for a <strong>WHILE</strong>” -> use for-loop when you know the number of loops at compile time.</li>\n<li>The syntax of a for-loop: <strong>for</strong> (<strong>Initialization</strong>: count = 1; <strong>Condition</strong>: count &#x3C;= limit; <strong>Increase</strong>: count = count +1) {<strong>Statement</strong>}</li>\n<li>Think carefully about the first &#x26; last loop.</li>\n<li>Write a <strong>for</strong> loop to repeat the game.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-cpp"><code class="language-cpp"><span class="token keyword">int</span> <span class="token function">main</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token comment">// introduce the game</span>\n  PrintIntro <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n  <span class="token comment">// get a guess from player and loop for number of turns</span>\n  <span class="token keyword">constexpr</span> <span class="token keyword">int</span> NUMBER_OF_TURNS <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token number">5</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n  <span class="token keyword">for</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">int</span> i <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> i <span class="token operator">&lt;</span> NUMBER_OF_TURNS<span class="token punctuation">;</span> i<span class="token operator">++</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n\t<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n\t\t<span class="token function">GetGuessAndPrintBack</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n    cout <span class="token operator">&lt;&lt;</span> endl<span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\t<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n\n  <span class="token keyword">return</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p><strong>Useful Links</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>* <a href="http://www.cplusplus.com/doc/tutorial/control">www.cplusplus.com</a></li>\n<li>* <a href="https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/b80153d8.aspx">msdn.microsoft.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id="clarity-is-worth-fighting-for"><a href="#clarity-is-worth-fighting-for" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Clarity is Worth Fighting For</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>More about levels of abstraction.</li>\n<li>A word on being clever.</li>\n<li>Using Visual Studio’s Extract “Extract Function”</li>\n<li>What a header file (.h) is.</li>\n<li>What’s refactoring, and why we do it.</li>\n<li>Removing side-effects.</li>\n<li>Where to find the course code. <a href="http://www.unrealcourse.com/">UnrealCourse</a> &#x26; <a href="https://github.com/UnrealCourse">Github.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Encapsulate for-loop in PlayGame() to clean up main():</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-cpp"><code class="language-cpp"><span class="token keyword">void</span> <span class="token function">PrintIntro</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token keyword">void</span> <span class="token function">PlayGame</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token operator">:</span>\nstring <span class="token function">GetGuessAndPrintBack</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n<span class="token keyword">int</span> <span class="token function">main</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  PrintIntro <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  PlayGame <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n  <span class="token keyword">return</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment">//Exit application</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n\n<span class="token keyword">void</span> <span class="token function">PlayGame</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token comment">// get a guess from player and loop for number of turns</span>\n  <span class="token keyword">constexpr</span> <span class="token keyword">int</span> NUMBER_OF_TURNS <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token number">5</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  <span class="token keyword">for</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">int</span> i <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> i <span class="token operator">&lt;</span> NUMBER_OF_TURNS<span class="token punctuation">;</span> i<span class="token operator">++</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n\t<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n\t\t<span class="token function">GetGuessAndPrintBack</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n    cout <span class="token operator">&lt;&lt;</span> endl<span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\t<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>All functions should only do one thing - removing PrintBack from GetGuess:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-cpp"><code class="language-cpp"><span class="token keyword">void</span> <span class="token function">PlayGame</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token comment">// get a guess from player and loop for number of turns</span>\n  <span class="token keyword">constexpr</span> <span class="token keyword">int</span> NUMBER_OF_TURNS <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token number">5</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  <span class="token keyword">for</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">int</span> i <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> i <span class="token operator">&lt;</span> NUMBER_OF_TURNS<span class="token punctuation">;</span> i<span class="token operator">++</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n\t<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n\t\t<span class="token function">GetGuess</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n    string Guess <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token function">GetGuess</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n    cout <span class="token operator">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="token string">"Your guess was: "</span> <span class="token operator">&lt;&lt;</span> Guess <span class="token operator">&lt;&lt;</span> endl<span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\t<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n\nstring <span class="token function">GetGuess</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  cout <span class="token operator">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="token string">"Enter your guess: "</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  string Guess <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token string">""</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  <span class="token function">getline</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>cin<span class="token punctuation">,</span> Guess<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  <span class="token keyword">return</span> Guess<span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>To rename all instances of a function identifier in VisualStudio, select it and press <strong>CTRL+R</strong> twice!</p>\n<h3 id="booleans-and-comparisons"><a href="#booleans-and-comparisons" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Booleans and comparisons</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>What a boolean is, and how to use it.</li>\n<li>Only use when completely clear what you mean.</li>\n<li>Use <strong>==</strong> for comparison.</li>\n<li>Use <strong>&#x26;&#x26;</strong> for logical AND.</li>\n<li>Use <strong>||</strong> for logical OR.</li>\n<li>Use <strong>[n]</strong> to access a string, starting at n=0.</li>\n<li>Use <strong>‘ ‘</strong> for characters, and <strong>“ “</strong> for strings.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Add true/false boolean for asking to restart the game after a completed run.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-cpp"><code class="language-cpp"><span class="token keyword">void</span> <span class="token function">PrintIntro</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token keyword">void</span> <span class="token function">PlayGame</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token operator">:</span>\nstring <span class="token function">GetGuessAndPrintBack</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token keyword">bool</span> <span class="token function">AskToPlayAgain</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n<span class="token keyword">int</span> <span class="token function">main</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  PrintIntro <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  PlayGame <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  <span class="token function">AskToPlayAgain</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n  <span class="token keyword">return</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment">//Exit application</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n\n<span class="token keyword">bool</span> <span class="token function">AskToPlayAgain</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  cout <span class="token operator">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="token string">"Do you want to play again? y/n "</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  string Response <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token string">""</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  <span class="token function">getline</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>cin<span class="token punctuation">,</span> Response<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n  <span class="token keyword">return</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>Response<span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span> <span class="token operator">==</span> <span class="token string">\'y\'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">||</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>Response<span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span> <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token string">\'Y\'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Response[0] takes the first character from the Response string. Compare to character y/Y and return true or false.</p>\n<h3 id="using-do-and-while-in-c"><a href="#using-do-and-while-in-c" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Using do and while in C++</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A <strong>do while</strong> loop is: do {code to repeat} while (condition);</li>\n<li>A do/while code is always executed at least once and repeated until the condition is reached.</li>\n<li>Making our game play multiple times.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-cpp"><code class="language-cpp"><span class="token keyword">int</span> <span class="token function">main</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token keyword">bool</span> bPlayAgain <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token boolean">false</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n  <span class="token keyword">do</span>\n  <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n    PrintIntro <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n    PlayGame <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n    bPlayAgain <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token function">AskToPlayAgain</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n  <span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n\n  <span class="token keyword">while</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>bPlayAgain<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n\n  <span class="token keyword">return</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>The boolean bPlayAgain is set to <strong>false</strong> at the beginning of the loop - AskToPlayAgain sets it to <strong>true</strong> if player types “yes”.\nThe do/while loop is repeated until while is set to false.</p>',fields:{slug:"/unreal-engine-coding-standards-part-iii/",prefix:"2017-06-19"},frontmatter:{title:"Unreal Engine Coding Standards (III)",subTitle:"The Unreal Engine Developer Course - Learn C++ & Make Games. Learn C++ from scratch. How to make your first video game in Unreal engine. Gain confidence in programming.",cover:{childImageSharp:{resize:{src:"/static/photo-34477006171_65093dd884_o-cover-5fa4c34a6815a8cf5a8a5146d4a3caf8-ada8c.jpg"}}}}},author:{id:"E:/gatsby-starter-personal-blog/content/parts/author.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p><strong>Mike Polinowski</strong> Proin ornare ligula eu tellus tempus elementum. Aenean <a href="/contact/">contact me</a> iaculis mi, nec blandit lacus interdum vitae. Vestibulum non nibh risus, a scelerisque purus. :hearts:</p>'},footnote:{id:"E:/gatsby-starter-personal-blog/content/parts/footnote.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<ul>\n<li>This is a personal Developer Blog</li>\n<li>Ξ</li>\n<li>built by <a href="https://github.com/mpolinowski">Mike Polinowski</a></li>\n<li>Ξ</li>\n<li>with <a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.org/">Gatsby</a> &#x26; <a href="https://reactjs.org">React</a></li>\n<li>Ξ</li>\n<li>source code on <a href="https://github.com/mpolinowski/mpolinowski.github.io">GitHub</a></li>\n<li>Ξ</li>\n<li>deliverd by <a href="https://pages.github.com">Github Pages</a></li>\n<li>Ξ</li>\n<li>photos from <a href="https://www.flickr.com/people/149680084@N06/">Flickr</a></li>\n</ul>'}},pathContext:{slug:"/unreal-engine-coding-standards-part-iii/"}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---unreal-engine-coding-standards-part-iii-f8e3018b0cfb18019b41.js.map